      "content": "But the \"socio-economic factors\" you're talking about are basically just racial proxies. If we keep using those, we're just reinforcing systemic inequality under the guise of \"accuracy.\" How do you justify prioritizing predictive precision over the actual ethical impact on these communities? Isn't it more important to be fair than to be \"accurate\" based on historically biased data?",
